      <!-- START THE FEATURETTES -->

      <hr class="featurette-divider">

      <div class="featurette">
        <img class="featurette-image pull-right" width="40%" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/fromus/blog_posts/photos_taken_by_year.png">
        <h2 class="featurette-heading">One billion photos per day<span class="muted">, you love them all</span></h2>
        <p class="lead">Why should we have to choose only a few of our precious photos to view in the cloud? We want them all.</p>
      </div>

      <hr class="featurette-divider">

      <div class="featurette">
        <img class="featurette-image pull-left" src="../assets/img/examples/browser-icon-firefox.png">
        <h2 class="featurette-heading">Why do we have to organize them  <span class="muted">manually?</span></h2>
        <p class="lead">Each photo contains so many clues on how to organize them, such as dates, gps, people. Especially if we combine the information from different sources effectively. Instead of trying to manually sort pictures in different folders and drives, just connect them to us and we will organize them all for you.</p>
      </div>

      <hr class="featurette-divider">

